The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | In the City
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                      IN THE CITY
                  
	 Hosts India had a rich haul on the final day to nose ahead of Bangladesh and clinch the overall championship in the 3rd Indo-Bangla Games.       
	India claimed 10 gold, seven silver and seven bronze medals, with a major share coming in badminton, to finish with 32 gold, 27 silver and 26 bronze medals and pip Bangladesh in the championship that concluded here on Sunday.       
	It was a clean sweep in badminton for India shuttlers with Subhankar Dey beating Arup Baidya 21-17, 22-20 to clinch the mens singles title while Barnali Raha outplayed Amrita Mukherjee 21-12, 21-13 to bag the womens title.       
	Bangladesh had a share of 28 gold, 29 silver and 29 bronze medals with the last day yielding two gold, three silver and five bronze medals.                
